
<div metal:use-macro="layout">
    <div metal:fill-slot="content">

    <style>
      body {
        padding-top: 60px; /* 60px to make the container go all the way to the bottom of the topbar */
      }

      .container-molecules {
        margin: 0 auto;
        max-width: 700px;
      }

      .show-grid {
        margin-top: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .show-grid [class*="span"] {
        background-color: #eee;
        text-align: center;
        -webkit-border-radius: 3px;
           -moz-border-radius: 3px;
                border-radius: 3px;
        min-height: 40px;
        line-height: 40px;
      }
      .show-grid [class*="span"]:hover {
        background-color: #ddd;
      }
      .show-grid .show-grid {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }
      .show-grid .show-grid [class*="span"] {
        margin-top: 5px;
      }
      .show-grid [class*="span"] [class*="span"] {
        background-color: #ccc;
      }
      .show-grid [class*="span"] [class*="span"] [class*="span"] {
        background-color: #999;
      }

      div.row-fluid [class*="span"] .center-in-span { 
         float: none; 
         margin: 0 auto; 
         text-align: center; 
         display: block; 
         width: auto; 
         height: auto;
      }

      div.blah {
        display: inline-block;
        margin:20px;
        border:solid 1px;
        -webkit-border-radius: 7px;
           -moz-border-radius: 7px;
                border-radius: 7px;
        border-color:#bbbbbb;
        min-height: 40px;
        line-height: 40px;
        width: 220px; 
        height:119px; 
        background-size:220px 119px; 
        background-repeat:no-repeat;
      }

      div.blah:hover {
        background-color: #ddd;
      }
    </style>

    <script src="//code.jquery.com/ui/1.10.4/jquery-ui.js"></script>
    <script>
      // Executed by jQuery when the DOM is ready
      $( document ).ready(function() {
        //console.log( "ready!" );


      });

    </script>


    <div class="container">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>This project is developed by the <a href="http://www.ryerson.ca">Ryerson University</a> <a href="http://scs.ryerson.ca/">Computer Science Department</a> under the LTEF grant from the <a href="http://www.ryerson.ca/lt">Learning and Teaching office</a>.</p>
      <h3>People</h3>
      <p>Vitaliy Batusov - lead developer</p>
      <p>Dr. Mikhail Soutchanski - idea, requirements specification</p>
      <p>Dr. Andrew McWilliams - requirements specification</p>
      <h3>Technology</h3>
      <p>The back-end logic is developed in Python. The website is served by <a href="http://www.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid/about">Pyramid</a>. The source code for the project is open and available as a <a href="https://github.com/vbatusov/ltef-chemistry">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
      <p><a href="http://ggasoftware.com">GGA Software</a> - chemical object rendering via <a href="http://ggasoftware.com/opensource/indigo">Indigo Toolkit</a></p>
      <p><a href="http://www.chemaxon.com">ChemAxon</a> - initial reaction descriptions</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
